right after I fired you,

572
00:29:24,054 --> 00:29:26,013
but I couldn't admit it.

573
00:29:27,683 --> 00:29:31,686
I screwed everything up. I hope
that we can still work together.

574
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:39,944
Something's wrong
with her liver.

575
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:42,155
Blood flow's backing up,
spilling into her esophagus.

576
00:29:42,239 --> 00:29:44,031
From the cancer?
This isn't lymphoma.

577
00:29:44,116 --> 00:29:45,116
We don't know what it is.

578
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,284
We can wrap bands
around the veins,

579
00:29:46,368 --> 00:29:47,952
but the bleed is so bad,
that might not work.

580
00:29:48,036 --> 00:29:49,662
We want to try something
called the TIPS,

581
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:52,123
a shunt that makes the
blood bypass the liver.

582
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:53,291
That'll save her?

583
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:54,959
It should help preserve
her liver and heart.

584
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:57,712
But the liver cleans out
toxins, so bypass it too long,

585
00:29:57,796 --> 00:29:59,357
she'll get brain damage,
eventually die.

586
00:29:59,381 --> 00:30:01,591
But that's still probably less
dangerous than bleeding out now.

587
00:30:01,675 --> 00:30:03,009
Probably?

588
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:06,804
Valerie usually
makes the decisions...

589
00:30:06,889 --> 00:30:08,222
You gotta step up now.

590
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,852
Was she cheating on me?
I can't discuss...

591
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:16,230
Just tell me she wasn't lying.
Just tell me that.

592
00:30:21,904 --> 00:30:24,614
I'm supposed to
make this decision?

593
00:30:24,698 --> 00:30:26,824
I don't even know
who she is any more.

594
00:30:26,909 --> 00:30:29,535
Either way, you gotta
do it right now.

595
00:30:32,372 --> 00:30:34,582
Do whatever you think is right.

596
00:30:46,512 --> 00:30:48,846
I'd give her a day,
two days at the most.

597
00:30:48,931 --> 00:30:52,517
Great. You be the clock, everyone
else will be the doctors.

598
00:30:52,601 --> 00:30:53,851
Heart, kidneys, now liver.

599
00:30:53,936 --> 00:30:54,977
Amyloidosis.

600
00:30:55,062 --> 00:30:58,189
No speckles on the MRI. Alpha-1
antitrypsin deficiency?

601
00:30:58,273 --> 00:30:59,398
Too much kidney failure.

602
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:01,776
Primary hepatic fibrosis.

603
00:31:03,529 --> 00:31:06,447
It's our best guess.
Start her on steroids.

604
00:31:06,532 --> 00:31:08,652
Even if we're right, the
liver's probably too scarred.

605
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:09,700
We got to list her
for a new one.

606
00:31:09,785 --> 00:31:11,118
With an unconfirmed diagnosis?

607
00:31:11,245 --> 00:31:12,703
Not gonna happen. How
about a family member?

608
00:31:12,788 --> 00:31:14,205
I don't think the husband's
the right blood type.

609
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:16,582
Even if he was, he's not
going to give his liver now.

610
00:31:16,667 --> 00:31:17,875
He left her, I assume?

611
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,126
Not yet.

612
00:31:19,836 --> 00:31:22,380
He says he won't abandon
her while she's sick.

613
00:31:22,464 --> 00:31:24,215
She have any other
family members?

614
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:26,140
No one's going to risk
their life to save hers.

615
00:31:26,218 --> 00:31:28,844
Man, one false accusation
from a psychopath,

616
00:31:28,929 --> 00:31:30,888
and you turn out
to be a real bummer.

617
00:31:30,973 --> 00:31:34,141
I'm gonna go see if
Wilson has any liver left.

618
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:48,072
What are you doing?

619
00:31:48,156 --> 00:31:51,701
Paying Wibberly's mortgage
for a few months.

620
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:54,579
Congratulations on another
successful round of hectoring.

621
00:31:54,663 --> 00:31:57,623
Wait a minute. Is that
actually a check for him?

622
00:31:57,708 --> 00:32:01,085
No, it's a giant novelty item
for winning the lottery,

623
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:03,296
you're just standing
really far away.

624
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:07,133
Of all the people to go the
extra mile for, why this guy?

625
00:32:07,217 --> 00:32:10,886
I don't know, he just kind of
smells good and makes me laugh.

626
00:32:10,971 --> 00:32:14,140
Why not Cuddy? You never apologized
after you defaced her photo.

627
00:32:14,224 --> 00:32:16,934
Maybe because I recognize that
sending someone to the poorhouse

628
00:32:17,019 --> 00:32:19,520
is a little more serious
than editing a snapshot.

629
00:32:19,605 --> 00:32:22,273
No, it's because Cuddy actually
means something to you,

630
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:24,442
which makes it much
harder to apologize.

631
00:32:26,403 --> 00:32:29,572
If it'll make you shut up, I will
tell her I'm sorry about the photo.

632
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:31,991
Forget the photo. House,
she was in love with you.

633
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:34,160
And all she got
in return was abuse.

634
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,704
For years, you toyed
with her emotions.

635
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:37,955
She wasn't in love with me.

636
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:41,208
The fact that you still can't
admit it just proves my point.

637
00:32:41,293 --> 00:32:44,086
What do you want? Helping
the guy was your idea.

638
00:32:44,171 --> 00:32:46,213
No, help the guy, whatever.

639
00:32:46,298 --> 00:32:50,051
I'm just pointing out that it's
much easier to soothe your guilt

640
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:51,844
by throwing money at a stranger

641
00:32:51,928 --> 00:32:55,598
than by making amends to a
person you actually care about.

642
00:32:55,682 --> 00:32:58,017
You had me at "much easier."

643
00:32:58,101 --> 00:33:00,770
I'm going to pretend
to go to work now.

644
00:33:04,733 --> 00:33:06,025
Ping.

645
00:33:27,798 --> 00:33:29,090
Sarah?

646
00:33:30,342 --> 00:33:32,343
I'm Dr. Hadley.
I'm sorry to bother you,

647
00:33:32,427 --> 00:33:34,147
but I was told that
you're Valerie's sister.

648
00:33:34,221 --> 00:33:35,221
Mmm.

649
00:33:35,305 --> 00:33:38,140
I was just surprised
you came to visit.

650
00:33:39,935 --> 00:33:42,186
So is the rest of my family.

651
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:45,022
I was even more surprised
you got tested as a donor.

652
00:33:45,107 --> 00:33:46,190
Wrong blood type.

653
00:33:46,274 --> 00:33:50,152
But why? I mean,
you know what she's like.

654
00:33:50,237 --> 00:33:52,113
She's not that bad.

655
00:33:52,197 --> 00:33:53,739
Yes. She is.

656
00:33:57,661 --> 00:34:00,162
Our dad was a mean drunk.

657
00:34:01,248 --> 00:34:02,707
I was the older sister.

658
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:06,752
I was supposed to stand up for
her, not the other way around.

659
00:34:07,337 --> 00:34:09,922
She protected you
when you were kids?

660
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:13,509
Yeah. And then all of a
sudden, all of his crap

661
00:34:14,428 --> 00:34:18,806
and all his abuse,
it just changed her.

662
00:34:19,266 --> 00:34:20,975
It made her cold.

663
00:34:22,644 --> 00:34:23,728
When?

664
00:34:28,275 --> 00:34:30,818
We were wrong. Psychopathy
is a symptom.

665
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:33,112
I spoke to her sister. She
wasn't always like this.

666
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:36,157
She changed, and right
around adolescence.

667
00:34:38,201 --> 00:34:44,540
So, liver, heart, brain lie
dormant, and it starts at puberty.

668
00:34:51,256 --> 00:34:56,218
The raw food diet made it go fulminant.
Nuts are high in copper.

669
00:34:57,012 --> 00:34:58,763
It's Wilson's disease.

670
00:34:58,847 --> 00:35:01,766
We ruled that out.
No Keyser-Fleischer rings.

671
00:35:03,393 --> 00:35:07,354
There is one other sign. I know
there are lipstick lesbians.

672
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:10,900
Are there
nail-polish-remover bisexuals?

673
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:15,946
She's not supposed to be here.

674
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:17,239
As a doctor.

675
00:35:17,324 --> 00:35:20,826
You didn't say anything about her
capacity as a beautician's assistant.

676
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:37,593
Her fingernail's blue?

677
00:35:37,677 --> 00:35:38,803
Yep.

678
00:35:38,887 --> 00:35:40,888
Start her on chelation.

679
00:35:41,765 --> 00:35:43,057
What just happened?

680
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:44,350
You're gonna get better.

681
00:35:44,434 --> 00:35:47,311
Your body has an inability
to process copper.

682
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:49,980
It caused all of your problems.

683
00:35:50,065 --> 00:35:51,690
Even what's wrong
with your brain.

684
00:35:51,775 --> 00:35:54,151
That's going to change, too?

685
00:35:54,236 --> 00:35:57,404
It's probably rewired her
neurons permanently by now.

686
00:35:57,489 --> 00:35:59,240
But it's possible?

687
00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:02,076
Maybe.

688
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:03,911
I have to go get
the chelation equipment.

689
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:06,914
Bill, I need you
to sign some forms.

690
00:36:14,256 --> 00:36:16,507
You don't see what she's doing?

691
00:36:16,591 --> 00:36:19,176
She's laying the groundwork
to get her treatment,

692
00:36:19,261 --> 00:36:22,012
wake up a completely
different person

693
00:36:22,097 --> 00:36:26,016
so that you and all of
your money stay with her.

694
00:36:26,101 --> 00:36:27,977
It's a lie.

695
00:36:28,061 --> 00:36:29,270
You said there was a chance.

696
00:36:29,354 --> 00:36:32,147
Okay, there's a teeny chance.

697
00:36:32,232 --> 00:36:36,235
But even if it cures her, it's
not going to make her love you.

698
00:36:39,781 --> 00:36:41,532
I was happy before.

699
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:47,621
I know, and I'm sorry,
but it wasn't real.

700
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:50,332
It felt real.

701
00:36:54,796 --> 00:36:56,338
I don't know...

702
00:36:58,967 --> 00:37:01,093
Maybe that can be enough.

703
00:37:12,397 --> 00:37:14,773
You're really
doing this for me?

704
00:37:16,902 --> 00:37:18,319
Tax shelter.

705
00:37:20,155 --> 00:37:22,114
I'll take some
of that chili now.

706
00:37:28,413 --> 00:37:29,830
I can't accept this.

707
00:37:29,915 --> 00:37:31,707
Fine, forget the chili.

708
00:37:32,584 --> 00:37:34,168
Bye, Wibberly.

709
00:37:34,586 --> 00:37:37,004
I got an A plus
with your paper.

710
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:44,261
I was an orthopedic surgeon for
10 years at New York Mercy.

711
00:37:44,346 --> 00:37:46,096
I had a gambling problem.

712
00:37:46,181 --> 00:37:49,099
I tried to cover it by overbilling
some Medicare patients.

713
00:37:49,184 --> 00:37:52,269
Lost my license.
That's why I'm here.

714
00:37:52,354 --> 00:37:54,104
Not because of you.

715
00:37:54,189 --> 00:37:56,273
Why are you
telling me this now?

716
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:00,540
Because I thought
you'd be the same bastard

717
00:38:00,612 --> 00:38:03,322
you were in med school, but...

718
00:38:15,460 --> 00:38:16,460
Keep it.

719
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:18,629
No. I can get another place.

720
00:38:18,713 --> 00:38:21,298
Just take it.
I screwed you over.

721
00:38:21,383 --> 00:38:22,800
You got me an A plus.

722
00:38:22,884 --> 00:38:24,301
Take it. No.

723
00:38:24,386 --> 00:38:28,097
Do I have to shove it down your throat?
Take the damn check!

724
00:38:54,082 --> 00:38:55,874
Your vitals are up.

725
00:38:58,920 --> 00:38:59,962
Treatment's working.

726
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,547
I'm not sure we can
fix your liver,

727
00:39:01,631 --> 00:39:04,925
but we can definitely
list you for a new one.

728
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,762
When you're better, we're
gonna take a long vacation.

729
00:39:08,847 --> 00:39:10,681
You want to go to Vietnam,
one of the beaches?

730
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:14,685
We're gonna get a hut, just you
and me, nothing to worry about.

731
00:39:18,773 --> 00:39:20,441
You're pathetic.

732
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:25,070
What?

733
00:39:25,155 --> 00:39:29,742
I mean, when you had a suspicion,
fine, but you know now.

734
00:39:29,826 --> 00:39:31,785
How can you be this pitiful?

735
00:39:33,163 --> 00:39:35,581
You don't mean this.
You're sick.

736
00:39:35,665 --> 00:39:36,915
I'm not sick.

737
00:39:38,126 --> 00:39:40,210
I almost died,
and I still might.

738
00:39:40,295 --> 00:39:42,379
And who knows, maybe
it's focusing my mind

739
00:39:42,464 --> 00:39:44,882
because the idea of spending the
rest of my life with you...

740
00:39:44,966 --> 00:39:46,300
Valerie...

741
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:05,569
Why'd you do that?

742
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:06,945
Because he's pathetic.

743
00:40:07,530 --> 00:40:09,281
He hasn't changed.

744
00:40:14,496 --> 00:40:19,124
But you have. The treatment
actually worked on your brain.

745
00:40:19,209 --> 00:40:20,449
If you were still a psychopath,

746
00:40:20,460 --> 00:40:22,211
you would have just
kept draining him dry.

747
00:40:22,295 --> 00:40:23,295
What do you want?

748
00:40:23,379 --> 00:40:25,380
